<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4836635>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figs. 10–17. Scanning electron micrographs of characters in Olibroporus punctatus. 10) Right eye and antenna (scale bar = 100 μm); 11) Right elytron (scale bar = 1 mm); 12) Detail of elytral surface showing punctures and microsculpture (scale bar = 100 μm); 13) Elytral subbasal line showing crenulate cuticular projections (scale bar = 20 μm); 14) Prosternal process (scale bar = 100 μm); 15) Central part of mesoventrite showing “mesoventral plate” and metaventral process (scale bar = 100 μm); 16) Metaventrite showing area around left mesocoxal cavity (scale bar = 100 μm); 17) Metatarsus (scale bar = 100 μm). Specimen from 3.2 km S Sebring, Highlands Co., Florida (FSCA)." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4836635/files/figure.png" .

